# Development Workflow Documents

Every non-trivial feature or fix follows a **3-document flow** stored under `docs/development/`.

## 1. Development Plan (`docs/development/plans/`)

Required sections:
- Objective and current situation
- Technical approach — evaluate multiple options, state the chosen one with rationale
- Architecture design (diagrams / code structure where helpful)
- Implementation phases with priorities
- Success metrics (quantitative + qualitative)

Awaits approval before proceeding to task breakdown.

## 2. Tasks Breakdown (`docs/development/tasks/`)

Required per task:
- Task ID, priority, estimated time, dependencies
- Numbered steps with code snippets
- Completion criteria checklist

## 3. Implementation Summary (`docs/development/summaries/`)

Written after completion:
- What was implemented (table of done tasks)
- Files created / modified
- Usage examples
- Known limitations / next steps

## When to use this flow

Any feature that spans more than one file or more than ~2 hours of work.
